		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><date>Decbr. 7<hi rend="sup">Th</hi> 1862</date>.</p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Is. Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
				<p>Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I received the Occident<lb/> yesterday&#8212;which was the first<lb/> intimation I had from you that<lb/> you had received my letter.<lb/>  I supposed a letter from a<lb/> lady was worthy a reply.<lb/>  I do not know on what terms<lb/> you have inserted the adver&#45;<lb/>tisement&#59; it is of no importance<lb/> and&#44; as I wish to discontinue<lb/> advertising in your columns&#8212;as in<lb/> the <hi rend="underline">insulting</hi> manner&#44; you have<lb/> published the same&#44; you would render<lb/> me more injury than service&#58;<lb/> you are the same Sir&#44; as the<lb/> rest of the world&#8212;a <hi rend="underline">friend</hi> in<lb/> prosperity but ready to add a pang<lb/> to the mind of a man in adversity</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>Is this your lesson of religion&#63;<lb/>  You will please discontinue<lb/> the advertisement and send<lb/> the Bill if you have any<lb/> against <hi rend="underline">me</hi> to <persName>Revd. S M Isaacs</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">Yours respectfully</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">Hannah Simons</persName></p>
				<p><placeName>21 &#38; 22. Mansfield Place</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>W. 57<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Street</placeName>.</p>
		</body>
